s cleric idiot</span><hr size=1> A &quot;donation&quot; for a service, I have always seen as:<br>
<br>
1) Recognition of the time to raise a class that is equipped to help others, and of the accomplishment of reaching the appropriate level and the played time involved.  In the case of a click-rez, this also applies to the accomplishment of attaining the epic.<br>
<br>
2) Recognition of the character's time and Mana.  Mana is &quot;free&quot;, but mana is also time.  And time is not free.  In the particular case of KEI, recognition of the fact that it costs 900 mana (yes, the enchanter gets the mana regen benefits from the same cast, but more on this later).<br>
<br>
3) In the case of KEI, recognition of the (sometimes) months spent saving (what used to be) 70k for a single spell scroll.<br>
<br>
4) In the case of KEI, recognition of the fact that KEI is almost like remote power-leveling.  At extremely low levels, it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>is</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> power-leveling.  It is four hours of reduced, even eliminated down time. (Even c1 eliminates downtime at level 4 from my experience)<br>
<br>
So, why a minimum charge?  Simply put, everyone wants KEI.  Ever just sit in Knowledge for a while?  Occasionally if no one has been shouting that they are casting KEI, you'll see a scrolling of requests for it.  Why does this make a difference?<br>
<br>
At my current level (56) I *might* have 2700 mana for three casts; granted I will have more at 60, but I've largely focused in certain other areas, since going oom is very seldom an issue for me.  When left to donation, people don't realize this, apparently.  You might make 10pp on a cast, if people bother donating.  Back before KEI came out, I never /ooc'd about casting, but when I did c/c2 on request, I got a donation maybe one cast out of twenty.  Due to the sheer volume of people requesting KEI, an enchanter could quickly become simply a buff machine for everyone else with little or no reward for their time spent.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, many enchanters still cast for donations, and occasionaly there's a free MGB of KEI on Innoruuk server.  I hope this indicates that there are still many people who acknowledge the four points above.  I'm not advocating 100pp per cast; I'm saying, consider their effort, and be fair.<br>
<br>
KEI'ers who are also tradeskillers should consider other options for lower level characters.  Perhaps a stack of some low-level component that you need in exchange for the cast, since the KEI'er would otherwise have to farm the components him/herself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drainer>Drainer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(5/19/03 8:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A tale of Enchanter Greed...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Oh one final note to all you people who do ask for KEI from an Enchanter. Please don't be /anon or /roleplaying when you ask. Maybe nobody else feels this way, but I just find it a great annoyance when someone is hiding their class and level (more then likely to avoid beggars) begs for me to buff them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
