<br>
Every now and then, she would go to the local marketplace, and have a look at the wares for sale, and every now and then a scroll called Koadic's Endless Intellect would be up for sale. Every time, it was up for 50.000 platinum pieces. The young enchantress continued to save, to be able to buy this spell.<br>
<br>
One day, she reached the 60th level of exsistance, and she ran to the bazaar, again in search of the elusive spell. When she arrived, she spotted a copy of the spell for sale for 40.000 latinum pieces. What a bargain! But alas, she had only 15.000 if the shiny metallic coins.<br>
<br>
Out of the blue, a friend steps, and offers her the remaning 25.000 platinum pieces. She thinks about it for a while, but they agree, that she will pay him back as soon as she can... She buys the spell... at the bargain price of 40.000 platinum pieces.<br>
<br>
She now spends her time online casting the spell on people around her, trying to get a donation for it, and hoping she will be able to pay back her friends kindness. If she is very lucky, she might get 500-1000 platinum pieces an hour. As she stands there, feeling like a crack dealer, feeding peoples unhealthy mana habits, she watches her friends go out and have fun...<br>
<br>
One day, she decides she is to put a price tag on her spell, or she will be there until she turns gray... And as she reads the boards of her classs, she sees this quote and she feels it justifies her actions...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What goes around comes around<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
