<br>
As for charging a set fee, I don't see the problem.  Just opens the door for someone else to come in and undercut the price.  On Luclin server, there is no shortage of enchanters willing and able to sell KEI.  I rarely do, since most times there are 2 people in nexus and a third in PoK selling it already.<br>
<br>
When I do sell it I never set a fee, just not my style.  If people are donating well, I'll stick around.  If I'm averaging less than 10p a person, I'll quickly move on.  Level 46+ players can certainly afford more than that and it isn't worth my time to sit there for such small change.  I can make more killing kobolds for fine steel.<br>
<br>
Again, it's economics and it is a service.  I happily pay 100p for HoV before I head to solo.  It makes my life easier and I feel I am paying well for the service some kind cleric is willing to give me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lagduffhairyfeet>Lagduff Hairyfeet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(7/13/03 1:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=53>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://lagduff.mine.nu/treehugger.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You must be joking!!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Hmm.. well sorry to see that Damerr has so much pent up anger toward enchanters<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
